==English==

{{rank|date|summer|simply|856|terrible|Tom|author|authority}}

===Adjective===
'''terrible'''

#[[dreadful]]; causing [[alarm]] and [[fear]].
#* The witch gave him a '''terrible''' curse.
#[[most]] [[formidable]].
#*'''1883:''' [[w:Robert Louis Stevenson|Robert Louis Stevenson]], ''[[w:Treasure Island|Treasure Island]]'' – ...and there was even a party of the younger men who pretended to admire him, calling him a "true sea-dog," and "real old salt," and such-like names, and saying there was the sort of man that made England '''terrible''' at sea.
#[[intense]]; [[extreme]] in [[degree]] or [[extent]].
#* He paid a '''terrible''' price for his life of drinking.
#[[unpleasant]], [[disagreeable]].
#* The food was '''terrible''' but it was free.
#[[very]] [[bad]].
#* Whatever he thinks, he is a '''terrible''' driver.

